cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on leveraging human visual attention to improve decision making in a 3D navigation maze environment. This involves using saliency maps generated from images, which is a common technique in computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses training an agent to make decisions based on visual input, which is a common topic in AI research. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses the UNREAL architecture, which is a deep reinforcement learning algorithm, to train the agent. This falls under the category of machine learning. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper explores how humans selectively pay attention to certain parts of visual input, and how this can be leveraged to improve decision making in an AI agent. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses a deep reinforcement learning algorithm to train the agent, which involves neural networks. This falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing.
